 <fr:tex
display="block">    \epsilon ' x : \equiv     \epsilon \mathopen {} \left ( f \mathopen {} \left ( f ^{-1}  x \right ) \mathclose {} \right ) \mathclose {} ^{-1}   \cdot   \mathsf {act}_{ f } \mathopen {} \left ( \eta \mathopen {} \left ( f ^{-1}  x \right ) \mathclose {} \right ) \mathclose {}   \cdot   \epsilon  x  </fr:tex>

 <fr:p>The coherence <fr:tex>\chi \colon   \mathsf {act}_{ f } \circ   \eta   \sim   \epsilon ' \circ  f</fr:tex> can be constructed using our two naturality lemmas <fr:ref
